"{\"abstract\":\"The paper proposes a diversity-enhanced condensation algorithm to address the particle impoverishment problem which stochastic filtering usually suffers from. The particle diversity plays an important role as it affects the performance of filtering. Although the condensation algorithm is widely used in computer vision, it easily gets trapped in local minima due to the particle degeneracy. We introduce a modified evolutionary computing method, adaptive differential evolution, to resolve the particle impoverishment under a proper size of particle population. We apply our proposed method to endoscope tracking for estimating three-dimensional motion of the endoscopic camera. The experimental results demonstrate that our proposed method offers more robust and accurate tracking than previous methods. The current tracking smoothness and error were significantly reduced from (3.7, 4.8) to (2.3 mm, 3.2 mm), which approximates the clinical requirement of 3.0 mm.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"153220117\",\"name\":\"X. Lu\\u00f3\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/153220117\"},{\"authorId\":\"143674028\",\"name\":\"Y. Wan\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/143674028\"},{\"authorId\":\"1706670\",\"name\":\"X. He\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1706670\"},{\"authorId\":\"1688428\",\"name\":\"Jie Yang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1688428\"},{\"authorId\":\"144070506\",\"name\":\"K. Mori\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/144070506\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"143894131\",\"name\":\"W. Ingram\"},{\"authorId\":\"1807175\",\"name\":\"J. Yang\"},{\"authorId\":\"3996579\",\"name\":\"B. Beadle\"},{\"authorId\":\"32117089\",\"name\":\"R. Wendt\"},{\"authorId\":\"1849484\",\"name\":\"A. Rao\"},{\"authorId\":\"40178932\",\"name\":\"X. Wang\"},{\"authorId\":\"1918950\",\"name\":\"L. Court\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1371/